{"entries":[{"id":"classic-sarah-sze","name":"Sarah Sze","category":"藝術家","tier":"經典檔案庫","region":"西方","country":"美國","media":["裝置","數位/互動","建築/場域"],"works":"Triple Point；Shorter than the Day；Metronome","comment":"她擅長把碎片、影像與建築縫合成流動系統；公共性在於讓觀眾感到世界正在重組。","website":"https://www.sarahsze.com/","workPage":"https://www.sarahsze.com/","photo":"https://www.sarahsze.com/","classicTitle":"Shorter than the Day","classicImage":"https://media.architecturaldigest.com/photos/5efdbbabf4f8b984a52c826a/16:9/w_1280,c_limit/AD0720_SARAH_SZE_2.jpg","classicDesc":"Shorter than the Day 在機場公共空間中懸置細碎物件與影像邏輯，像一個正在運轉的宇宙模型。作品把移動、資訊碎片與全球交通的心理狀態凝成可觀看的系統。","status":"官方來源","updated":"2026-07-03"},{"id":"classic-susan-philipsz","name":"Susan Philipsz","category":"藝術家","tier":"經典檔案庫","region":"西方","country":"英國 / 德國","media":["聲音/霧/水","裝置","建築/場域"],"works":"Lowlands；Surround Me；War Damaged Musical Instruments","comment":"她把不可見的聲音變成公共場域的記憶裝置；適合用來理解非物件型公共藝術。","website":"https://www.susanphilipsz.com/","workPage":"https://www.susanphilipsz.com/","photo":"https://www.susanphilipsz.com/","classicTitle":"Lowlands","classicImage":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/07/King_George_V_Bridge%2C_Glasgow_-_geograph.org.uk_-_665391.jpg","classicDesc":"Lowlands 以藝術家清唱的聲音在橋下與河岸空間迴盪，使公共場域被記憶與失落感覆蓋。它證明公共藝術可以沒有可見物件，卻仍能精準改變一個地方的情緒。","status":"官方來源","updated":"2026-07-03"},{"id":"classic-rafael-lozano-hemmer","name":"Rafael Lozano-Hemmer","category":"藝術家","tier":"經典檔案庫","region":"西方","country":"墨西哥 / 加拿大","media":["數位/互動","光/影像/投影","社會參與"],"works":"Vectorial Elevation；Pulse Room；Border Tuner","comment":"他把公共藝術推進互動科技、監控與參與政治；觀眾的資料與身體常直接成為作品材料。","website":"https://www.lozano-hemmer.com/","workPage":"https://www.lozano-hemmer.com/","photo":"https://www.lozano-hemmer.com/bio.php","classicTitle":"Vectorial Elevation","classicImage":"https://www.lozano-hemmer.com/image_sets/vectorial_elevation/vitoria_gasteiz_2002/victorialelevation_vitoria_14_t.jpg","classicDesc":"Vectorial Elevation 讓網路參與者控制城市廣場上的光束，將個人指令轉化為公共天空景觀。它把互動藝術、城市尺度與資料參與整合在一起，是數位公共藝術的重要先例。","status":"官方來源","updated":"2026-07-03"},{"id":"classic-lee-bul","name":"Lee Bul / 李昢","category":"藝術家","tier":"經典檔案庫","region":"東亞","country":"韓國","media":["裝置","雕塑","建築/場域"],"works":"Willing To Be Vulnerable；Mon grand récit；Aubade","comment":"她把烏托邦建築、身體與科技焦慮做成巨大裝置；適合補足東亞公共藝術的未來主義面向。","website":"https://www.leebul.com/","workPage":"https://www.leebul.com/","photo":"https://www.leebul.com/","classicTitle":"Willing To Be Vulnerable","classicImage":"https://dza2a2ql7zktf.cloudfront.net/binaries-cdn/dqzqcuqf9/image/fetch/q_auto%2Cdpr_auto%2Cc_fill%2Cf_auto%2Cw_auto/https%3A//d2u3kfwd92fzu7.cloudfront.net/asset/cms/Art_Basel_Hong_kong_2019_Lee_Bul_15.jpg","classicDesc":"Willing To Be Vulnerable 以飛船般的巨大銀色結構呈現現代性、失敗烏托邦與技術慾望。作品既壯觀又不安，適合理解東亞當代藝術如何把未來想像轉成公共心理景觀。","status":"官方來源","updated":"2026-07-03"}]}